Select and filter
First, create a data frame with just the columns and rows you need to work with.

Select only the name, height, and species variables from the starwars data.
Filter that to include only rows with species of ‚ÄúHuman‚Äù, ‚ÄúDroid‚Äù, ‚ÄúGungan‚Äù and ‚ÄúWookiee‚Äù.
Save the results into a new data frame called characters and then print out the new characters data frame.












characters &lt;- starwars |&gt;
  select(name, height, species) |&gt;
  filter(species %in% c("Human", "Droid", "Gungan", "Wookiee"))

